  "title": "Exploring Novel Cropping Options for Pigeonpea in Chittagong District, Bangladesh. III, Population Response of Short-Duration Pigeonpea in Hilly Areas",
  "abstract": "In a field experiment in 1991/92 at Hathazari, Bangladesh, pigeonpeas cv. ICPL 151 were sown at densities of 2.5-40 plants/m² on 4 July. The highest yields were obtained at densities of 20 (1.88 t/ha) or 40 plants/m² (1.86 t).",
